title: Error `up-to-date` on datalad publish?
body:
#### What is the problem?
I am pushing some changes to a remote server. Had to try this a few times because some subdatasets weren't in the remote initially. Now the local and remote seem to be in sync when I check git log, but the publish call ends with this error:
```
[ERROR  ] failed to push to pushsibling: master -> pushsibling/master [rejected] (non-fast-forward); pushed: ['[up to date]'] [publish(/home/dp/datasets/apr26/freesurfer)]
publish(error): . (dataset) [failed to push to pushsibling: master -> pushsibling/master [rejected] (non-fast-forward); pushed: ['[up to date]']]
action summary:
  publish (error: 1, notneeded: 447)
```
Should I ignore this error since both repositories seem in sync from a git perspective?

#### What steps will reproduce the problem?
Not 100% sure of whether this is reproducible, I had to run publish multiple times while fixing some of the missing subdatasets in the remote.

#### What version of DataLad are you using (run `datalad --version`)? On what operating system (consider running `datalad wtf`)?
0.12.6

#### Is there anything else that would be useful to know in this context?
NA

#### Have you had any success using DataLad before? (to assess your expertise/prior luck.  We would welcome your testimonial additions to https://github.com/datalad/datalad/wiki/Testimonials as well)
All good.
